  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, these studies only provide limited constraint information to LLMs, containing the requirements, signature information, and restricted code dependencies, leading to a difference in programming information needs from humans.",
    "Some work targets real-world GitHub issues for code model to resolve, such as SWE-bench (Jimenez et al., 2023).",
    "To get closer to realistic programming scenarios, we formalize the repo-level code generation task and propose CODEAGENT to help LLMs handle this complex task.",
    "We construct a repo-level code generation benchmark CODEAGENTBENCH to evaluate our method and provide an analysis of benchmarks commonly used for these generation tasks in Table 7.",
    "Compared with existing code generation tasks, repo-level code generation is more consistent in real-world programming scenarios, fostering the evolvement of the code generation community."
